I said "Otis you have one pine cone."  We walked a little further and I kicked another one.  Natural, being a labrador, he ran and got it. "Otis, you have two pine cones. "  He had both in his mouth.  A few minutes later he came back with a third in his mouth.  "Otis?  Do you have three?"  Our walk ended.  We played this game a few times. One day I went out and said, "Otis get me one pine cone." Sure enough he came back with one.  Then I told him to get two.  Sure enough he came back with two pine cones in his mouth.
